Package: sharefs
Title: Fast Filesystem Operations for Network Shares
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Or", "Gadish", email = "orgadish@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Alternatives to base R's file listing, metadata, and
    copy functions, optimized specifically for reading files off an SMB/CIFS
    network share (a mapped network drive or UNC path) on Windows, where
    each individual file operation -- listing a directory, calling
    'stat()' on a file, copying a file -- pays a full network round trip.
    'sharefs' uses a single 'Get-ChildItem()' call via 'PowerShell' to
    list a directory together with file metadata, and 'robocopy' to
    stage files locally, instead of one call per file.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
OS_type: windows
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
